video.title: BAKI
video.synopsis: While martial arts champion Baki Hanma trains hard to surpass his legendary father, five violent death row inmates descend upon Tokyo to take him on.

episodes.synopsis: Underground martial arts promoter Tokugawa warns champion Baki that five violent death row escapees from around the world are all heading for Tokyo.
episodes.title: Synchronicity

episodes.synopsis: While Baki easily subdues the thugs hired by delinquents from his own school, death row escapee Spec pays a visit to assess the champion's abilities.
episodes.title: Dark Martial Arts

episodes.synopsis: Death row escapee Dorian barges into the Shinshinkai Dojo and is confronted by Sea King Retsu, who's there coaching students in Chinese martial arts.
episodes.title: They're Finally Here!!

episodes.synopsis: With all five death row escapees and their opponents assembled inside the underground arena, Tokugawa officially declares the beginning of battle.
episodes.title: The Battle Begins

episodes.synopsis: While out with Kozue, Baki is almost ambushed by Spec, but he's spared a fight when Kaoru suddenly appears to protect the couple from harm's way.
episodes.title: Want some more?

episodes.synopsis: Spec unleashes moves lethal enough to take out even the strongest of opponents in one strike, but Hanayama counters with improbable moves of his own.
episodes.title: Sergeant Katahira’s Report

episodes.synopsis: Ambushed by Doyle while in class, Baki leads Doyle away from the classroom only to encounter Yanagi in disguise outside.
episodes.title: A formidable team

episodes.synopsis: While Baki and his allies discuss the events that transpired at his school, Dorian appears, infiltrating Tokugawa's heavily guarded compound.
episodes.title: A match Vs. a true fight

episodes.synopsis: Kiyosumi Kato, known as one of the strongest fighters of Shinshinkai Karate, confronts Dorian deep inside his secret underground hideout.
episodes.title: Shaken Shinshinkai

episodes.synopsis: Boasting one million members nationwide, the Shinshinkai lures Dorian to an amusement park, where Kato's peer Suedo immediately strikes.
episodes.title: Air Duel

episodes.synopsis: As Dorian's past comes to light, Shinshinkai founder and "tiger killer" Doppo Orochi takes him on in an all-out karate versus kempo battle.
episodes.title: Tiger slayer

episodes.synopsis: Doppo Orochi pummels the life out of terror-stricken Dorian before bringing the equally injured Kiyosumi Kato over to administer the finishing blows.
episodes.title: Candy

episodes.synopsis: Deeming the escaped inmates a security threat to Tokyo, Police Chief Sonoda seeks help from law enforcement agency leaders from around the world.
episodes.title: Mr. Oliva

episodes.synopsis: Biscuit Oliva arrives in Tokyo to capture the remaining convicts. Sikorsky lures Baki into battle with help from an unlikely source.
episodes.title: Ungranted Freedom

episodes.synopsis: While searching the police database for clues, an unsuspecting Biscuit Oliva is ambushed by Doyle, who shows up dressed as a female police officer.
episodes.title: Tremendous muscle power

episodes.synopsis: Biscuit Oliva thinks he should get a black belt if he can score a point against every officer on the judo team, but Sonoda resists giving him one.
episodes.title: Slash

episodes.synopsis: The deadly fight between Kosho Shinogi and Doyle reaches its spectacular climax. Meanwhile, Yujiro pays a visit to an unsuspecting Baki and Kozue.
episodes.title: Dad!!

episodes.synopsis: Known as the pinnacle master of Chinese martial arts, Sea King Retsu displays his masterful use of weaponry against a fully armed Hector Doyle.
episodes.title: Thanks

episodes.synopsis: After setting off an explosion inside Shinshinkai's dojo, Doyle is confronted by its founder, Doppo. Tokugawa pays a visit to Ryukoh Yanagi's master.
episodes.title: Admission of defeat

episodes.synopsis: Tokugawa learns of the Poison Hand: the ultimate killer move of the "kudo" martial art form. Baki takes the next step in his relationship with Kozue.
episodes.title: Saga

episodes.synopsis: A newly invigorated Baki easily handles attacks from both Ryukoh Yanagi and Sikorsky, but before finishing them off, Baki makes an unusual move.
episodes.title: Punishment

episodes.synopsis: Baki's half-brother Jack Hammer challenges Sikorsky at a local park, where a battle inside the most inconceivable of places goes down.
episodes.title: Clash of the alphas

episodes.synopsis: In the underground battle arena, Gaia’s unorthodox fighting method slowly wears down Sikorsky.
episodes.title: The Real Attack

episodes.synopsis: With Ryukoh Yanagi's Poison Hand no longer a threat, Yujiro Hanma urges him to admit defeat against the sword-wielding jujutsu fighter Izo Motobe.
episodes.title: Defeat

episodes.synopsis: A legendary world heavyweight boxing champion reflects on his tense encounter with a young Yujiro Hanma.
episodes.title: God and the devil

episodes.synopsis: Retsu pleads with his mentor, Sea King Ryu, to grant a mortally poisoned Baki special entry into the Raitai martial arts tournament.
episodes.title: The Centennial Tournament

episodes.synopsis: Mohammad Alai Jr. tests a battle-eager Yujiro. Even though he's been poisoned, Sea King Retsu enters Baki into the Great Raitai Tournament in China.
episodes.title: Begin! The Centennial Tournament

episodes.synopsis: Alai Jr.'s deadly speed makes quick work of his opponent. A severely emaciated Baki faces Sea King Li, the greatest Poison Hand user in all of China.
episodes.title: Turnaround

episodes.synopsis: Sea Emperor Kaku is 121 years older than his opponent, but the legendary reigning champion doesn't hesitate to face Sea King Samwan in the arena.
episodes.title: Revived!

episodes.synopsis: Sea King Chin and Japan's sole Sea King, Jaku, battle on the tournament floor. Meanwhile, Baki provokes Yujiro into fighting him offstage.
episodes.title: Team Formed!

episodes.synopsis: Biscuit Oliva's sheer power is unrivaled, but Shobun Ron and his unconventional fighting stance are unbothered. It's brute strength versus iai kenpo.
episodes.title: Hand Pocket

episodes.synopsis: A genius of Chinese kenpo, Retsu is the superior fighter, but Jaku's dirty techniques and tactical prowess make him a formidable foe.
episodes.title: Excellennnnt!

episodes.synopsis: Sea Emperor Kaku is the embodiment of Chinese kenpo. Yujiro Hanma is known as the strongest creature on Earth. A battle unlike any other begins!
episodes.title: Kaioh

episodes.synopsis: Yujiro pits his raw power against Kaku's martial arts skills, which he's honed for over a century. The match's shocking outcome stuns everyone.
episodes.title: The Title of the Strongest

episodes.synopsis: Alai Jr. proposes to Kozue, who's dumbfounded. To prove he's a better man than Baki, Alai Jr. challenges the elderly aikido master Goki Shibukawa.
episodes.title: The Master vs the Boxer

episodes.synopsis: Alai Jr. continues testing his skill against notable fighters, but Baki's half-brother Jack Hammer is unlike any combatant he's faced before.
episodes.title: Stand and Fight

episodes.synopsis: Badly injured from his street fights, Alai Jr. returns to his hotel room. There his father, the greatest boxer of all time, challenges him to a match.
episodes.title: Awakening

episodes.synopsis: A battle between the sons of two legendary fighters begins deep below Tokyo Dome. It’s Baki versus Alai Jr., and the winner is anyone's guess.
episodes.title: Completion

episodes.synopsis: After Ryukoh Yanagi escapes from prison, Inspector Sonoda attempts to locate the other death row inmates who wreaked havoc on Tokyo.
episodes.title: Revenge Tokyo
